China said Tuesday it was willing to work with the world community on improving food security as it responded to growing global concerns about the safety of edible Chinese exports.
The Chinese government will continue to pay great attention to exported food safety, said an official with the country's quality control watchdog on Thursday.
The official said China has set up a complete monitoring system to ensure safety of exported food.
China's quality supervision authorities have blacklisted 14 companies for planning to export substandard food products and banned them from further exports.
